id: pm-16ue
title: "SDK describeExtensionActivation: single-call introspection of every registered surface (complements assert*/run*)"
description: "Add a describe/introspection verb to the SDK testing surface. ExtensionActivationResult already exposes per-surface COUNTS (hook_counts, registration_counts, *_count) but no single API enumerating WHAT was registered by name: a package author or agent must walk all 15+ sub-registries (registrations.commands/flags/item_types/item_fields/migrations/importers/exporters/search_providers/vector_store_adapters, commands.overrides/handlers, parsers/preflight/services/renderers.overrides, hooks.before/after/onWrite/onRead/onIndex) by hand to answer 'what does this extension register?'. describeExtensionActivation(activation, {extensionName?}) returns a flat, sorted, deterministic ExtensionActivationSummary of every surface's identifiers (command paths, hook kinds, item-type/field names, migration ids, importer/exporter/provider/adapter names, overridden service names + renderer formats, flag target-commands, preflight override count) plus the capabilities exercised (reusing collectUsedExtensionCapabilities). Value: (1) agents get one token-efficient call instead of traversing every sub-registry; (2) authors can assert their WHOLE registration surface in one deepEqual ('I register exactly these surfaces, nothing more' = a least-privilege check). Completes the author(define*) -> register(api.register*) -> verify-one(assert*) -> invoke-one(run*) -> enumerate-all(describe) ergonomics. New src/core/extensions/activation-summary.ts, re-exported via @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk and /sdk/testing, 100% line+branch+docstring coverage, documented in docs/SDK.md."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: agent-ux,"area:extensions","area:sdk",living-map,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-06-22T12:51:14.910Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-22T13:55:31.103Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: "Added src/core/extensions/activation-summary.ts exporting describeExtensionActivation(activation,{extensionName?}):ExtensionActivationSummary — a pure function that walks every activation sub-registry once and returns a flat, de-duplicated, locale-sorted (hooks in canonical lifecycle order) enumeration of all 16 registered-surface identifiers (commands/command_overrides/command_handlers, hooks, flag_commands, item_types/item_fields, migrations, importers/exporters, search_providers/vector_store_adapters, parser_overrides, service_overrides, renderer_overrides, preflight_overrides count) plus the exercised capabilities (reusing collectUsedExtensionCapabilities). Re-exported from the @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk barrel and the /sdk/testing subpath (barrel identity locked via toBe). Shares normalizeExtensionName (now exported from capability-usage.ts) on both filter sides so named surfaces and capabilities never disagree for a whitespace-padded stored name. Completes the author(define*)->register(api.register*)->verify-one(assertRegistered*)->invoke-one(runRegistered*ForTest)->enumerate-all(describe) ergonomics for the extension platform."
expected_result: Package authors and agents get the entire registration surface of an activation in one token-efficient call (a single deepEqual for least-privilege 'registers exactly these surfaces' checks) instead of walking 15+ sub-registries; the helper ships on @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk and /sdk/testing at 100% coverage with the build/typecheck clean.
actual_result: "Merged PR #343 (squash bf36f80d). Full suite 4850->4858 tests green at 100/100/100/100 coverage; tsc (src+packages) clean; static + docs-skills gates green; dist/sdk/{index,testing}.d.ts declare the helper. Bots: Gemini clean (no feedback), CodeRabbit [approve] (all 5 polish items resolved across 3 rounds — flag-union test, fifteen-plus wording, hooks-order doc accuracy, .trim() consistency declined+restructured to shared normalizeExtensionName, preflight_overrides numeric-field doc), Sourcery rate-limited, Codex not connected. Verified end-to-end in a temp dir: a real package imported describeExtensionActivation from @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk/testing, activated, and got the full surface + extensionName filter in one call."
